SCOPE — WHAT THIS LICENSE COVERS AND DOES NOT COVER

This License covers the Lorevox source code, original
documentation, prompts, schemas, user interface text, narrator
templates that ship with the codebase, and related project
materials owned by the copyright holder.

This License does NOT grant any rights to:
  - Private narrator data created or imported by an end user
  - Family records, genealogy documents, photographs, scans,
    audio recordings, video, transcripts, or memoir drafts
    produced or stored by Lorevox during use
  - Model weights or AI model checkpoints loaded by Lorevox
    at runtime
  - Voice recordings, voice clones, or TTS speaker assets
  - Personal archives or operator-curated content
  - Any data that crosses the system boundary between
    "what this codebase ships with" and "what an operator
    or narrator generates while using the running product"

End-user data, family content, and runtime-generated materials
are owned by the operator or narrator who created them, subject
to any separate agreement the operator and narrator may have
between themselves. Lorevox the software grants no claim over
such content.

