CONTRIBUTIONS

Contributions to Lorevox are accepted by invitation only.

Do not submit pull requests, patches, code, documentation, prompts,
schemas, assets, training data, examples, designs, or other materials
unless you have been explicitly invited to contribute.

Before any contribution is accepted, the contributor must sign a
separate Lorevox Contributor Assignment Agreement (see
CONTRIBUTING.md and the agreement template at
docs/contributor-assignment-agreement.md) or other written agreement
approved by the copyright holder.

A pull request, patch, issue comment, email, message, or other
submission does not create any obligation for the copyright holder
to accept, review, merge, publish, credit, compensate, or maintain
the contribution.

Uninvited contributions may be closed, deleted, ignored, or rejected
without review. Acceptance of an invited contribution is contingent
on a valid signed Contributor Assignment Agreement and remains at
the sole discretion of the copyright holder.

